#My shell scripting learning

1) ${sample%.*} - base name

  String manipulation of base characters or base name
  For ex: float=20.5, echo ${float%.*} gives 20
          filename="sample.txt", base_name=${filename%.*} gives sample

2) $# number of command line arguments passed to the script(Count the number of arguments excluding the script file)

3) declare -A user = '([key]="value")' // declarative associate array
   echo "Value for key:   ${user["key"]}"
4) $? - Exit status of the last executed command













                                
